1
00:00:03,720 --> 00:00:06,480
(For an adult who’s about to 
turn sixteen like me,) 

2
00:00:06,760 --> 00:00:10,360
(all my past summers 
were nowhere near exciting.)

3
00:00:11,160 --> 00:00:13,520
(But this summer is different.)

4
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:16,400
(I’m looking forward to it)

5
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:19,600
(because it’s the summer before 10th grade,)

6
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:22,920
(which everyone says 
is a huge turning point.)

7
00:00:24,080 --> 00:00:25,920
(Students choose their study programs,)

8
00:00:26,440 --> 00:00:28,280
(some old friends transfer away,) 

9
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:30,640
(new friends come in,)

10
00:00:32,560 --> 00:00:36,200
(and our hearts start racing
over something called first love.) 

11
00:00:36,520 --> 00:00:39,080
(I really want to know what that feels like.)

12
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:42,640
(But there’s no point overthinking it.)

13
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:45,720
(Someone like Ko doesn’t really want much.)

14
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:49,280
Ko, I’m going to see your dad at the market.

15
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:50,520
Watch the house for me.

16
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:52,320
Okay. See you later, Mom.

17
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:56,560
(Someone like Ko 
only cares about one thing.)

18
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,680
(Having fun!)

19
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:01,720
Guys, Majin Buu is awesome. Look.

20
00:01:01,720 --> 00:01:03,360
You should read Slam Dunk with me.

21
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:04,800
No way. Read it by yourself, Augar.

22
00:01:05,080 --> 00:01:05,880
Right, Ko?

23
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:07,440
Yeah. You can read it alone.

24
00:01:07,520 --> 00:01:09,520
We’re Saiyans, right, August?

25
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:13,000
Ow! Damn it!

26
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:16,840
What the heck?

27
00:01:18,520 --> 00:01:20,560
So someone finally moved in next door?

28
00:01:21,960 --> 00:01:22,680
I don’t know.

29
00:01:22,880 --> 00:01:24,960
I heard someone moved in two weeks ago, 
but haven’t seen them move their stuff in yet.  

30
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:26,920
Holy shit!

31
00:01:27,880 --> 00:01:28,960
It’s really good.

32
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:33,480
Try some.

33
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:37,440
You have it. I’m gonna read my manga.

34
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:42,800
Nnngh...

35
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,880
Nnngh...

36
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,440
Jeez.

37
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:51,800
Stretching so loud 
the whole neighborhood can hear you.

38
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,640
I’m your neighbor.

39
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:54,320
Is there anything I can help with?

40
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:55,760
You’ve got a lot of stuff.

41
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:56,920
Yeah, we do.

42
00:02:58,600 --> 00:02:59,960
What’s the neighbor doing, Mom?

43
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:04,160
What? Can’t you tell?

44
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:05,600
They’re moving in.

45
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:07,680
Maybe they’re free 
during the Songkran break, 

46
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:09,080
so they decided to move in now. 

47
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,600
If you need anything, let me know. 

48
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:11,440
I live right over there.

49
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:13,120
Don’t ask me. Go ask your dad.

50
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:14,240
Thank you so much for helping.

51
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:16,600
Dad literally knows 
everyone in this neighborhood.

52
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:18,720
Already being friendly on day one.

53
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:24,720
Ah! Looks like you want to help.

54
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:27,800
That’s my boy. My sweet boy.

55
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:28,920
Go help them out.

56
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:29,720
- Go on.
- What?

57
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:32,320
- Help them move in.
- I’m not helping.

58
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:37,280
Looks like the neighbors 
have a kid your age.

59
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,720
You two could be friends.

60
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:40,120
Friends?

61
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:43,000
Someone like Ko doesn’t 
just become friends with anyone.

62
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:46,000
If they want to be friends with me, 
they have to come to me first.

63
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,840
Ah! “Someone like Ko,” huh?

64
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:49,840
Yeah. Someone like Ko.

65
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:54,200
And someone like Ko
will sweep the floor for me.

66
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:56,560
Do it.

67
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:06,640
Hurry up.

68
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,040
Here. Let me get that.

69
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:37,760
Thanks, son.

70
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:48,800
Hey!

71
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:49,320
Hey.

72
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:51,640
You just swept me.

73
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:53,720
You asked me to sweep the floor. 

74
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:54,720
Get back inside.

75
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,200
Come on.

76
00:04:57,320 --> 00:04:58,160
What are you doing?

77
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,240
Sweeping.

78
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:07,000
That dude doesn’t look friendly. 

79
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,920
I don’t like his vibe at all.

80
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:10,880
You sure you don’t?

81
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:14,000
You’ve been talking about him
since before Augar even broke a sweat. 

82
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:18,400
Yeah. If I didn’t know better, 
I’d think you were his fan.

83
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:19,960
His fan, my ass!

84
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:23,040
Someone like Ko 
doesn’t become anyone’s fan.

85
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:25,280
No surprise there.

86
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:26,880
August, you bastard.

87
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:29,160
If you met him, you’d get what I mean.

88
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:35,400
What are you practicing so hard for, Augar?

89
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:37,240
We’re in 10th grade now. 

90
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:38,480
You should start taking things seriously.

91
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:41,680
I want to make the school team. 

92
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:43,560
Then it’s on to the national team.

93
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:47,240
And you, August? What are you gonna—

94
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:50,520
We’re in 10th grade now. Be serious.

95
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:53,760
Serious, my ass!

96
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:55,080
You’re still reading manga.

97
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:55,720
Yeah.

98
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:59,920
Because I’m gonna win
the Dragon Ball Biggest Fan trophy.

99
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:01,600
Dragon Ball Biggest Fan?

100
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:03,080
Gosh.

101
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,240
I’m sick of serious people. 

102
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:04,960
You guys are no fun.

103
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:06,080
You should take things more seriously.

104
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:07,480
We’re in 10th grade now, Ko.

105
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:09,600
Right.

106
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:11,480
Watch me.

107
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:16,800
A fluke.

108
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,720
Let’s go get some ice cream.

109
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:25,200
If you want some, come with me. My treat.

110
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:26,200
Thank you, sir.

111
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:34,960
So you don’t want that
Dragon Ball Biggest Fan trophy anymore?

112
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:40,560
If it’s meant to be mine, 
I don’t need to try that hard.

113
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:43,960
Come on, Augar.

114
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:46,520
Yeah. Hey, hold on to this for me.

115
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:49,120
Wait up!

116
00:06:49,640 --> 00:06:52,400
Catch up with me if you can, Augar, August.

117
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,440
Of course, I can.

118
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:57,440
Let’s do a wheelie.

119
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,080
Let’s do it.

120
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:03,840
You can bring the rest here.

121
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:04,440
Dad.

122
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:06,040
I’m getting ice cream from Uncle’s shop.

123
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:07,200
Don’t forget to pay before you leave.

124
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:08,000
Ko!

125
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,600
You still haven’t paid me back for last time.

126
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,240
Ko!

127
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:12,280
You’ve already hit your limit for the week. 

128
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,640
Let’s go swimming tomorrow.

129
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,200
Nah. I’m afraid I’ll get darker.

130
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,960
But I’m not.

131
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,520
Suit yourself.

132
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:22,360
See you.

133
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,360
See you.

134
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:32,200
Wow!

135
00:08:58,880 --> 00:08:59,360
Oops!

136
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:01,200
What are you doing?

137
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:04,240
What? Nothing.

138
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:07,080
I’m just walking home.

139
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:13,400
Are we close? Why talk to me so casually? 

140
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:25,400
7TH GRADE
(All my life, I’ve only had two close friends: Augar and August.)

141
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:26,280
Ko!

142
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:27,760
Catch up with us if you can!

143
00:09:27,760 --> 00:09:29,320
(Nothing to adjust to.) 

144
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,720
(Nothing to worry about.)

145
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,480
(We always have so much fun together!)

146
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:34,400
Come on!

147
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,640
Attack the opponent!

148
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:45,640
What? 

149
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:46,600
Your character’s overpowered.

150
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,640
How am I supposed to beat that?

151
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:49,360
No, no, no, no.

152
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,480
Don’t make excuses, kiddo.

153
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:53,080
And what are you supposed to call me?

154
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,600
All right, Boss Ko.

155
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:56,920
Very good.

156
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:59,240
You can have them back.

157
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:01,560
Ko.

158
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,200
The teacher put me in charge.

159
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,920
Keep it down, or I’m writing your name up. 

160
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:19,120
“Keep it down, or I’m writing your name up.”

161
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:19,680
Ko!

162
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:22,120
I’m just teasing.

163
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:26,160
Let’s keep playing.

164
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:27,520
176.

165
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:30,120
[GRADE 7, CLASS 8]

166
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:34,680
Hello, sir.

167
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:38,280
171.

168
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:42,840
Wow, you boys are studying really hard.

169
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:45,040
Take a break and have some watermelon.

170
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:48,720
Shh. I’m concentrating.

171
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:50,000
Ah.

172
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:51,320
All right, sorry. 

173
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:52,120
I won’t bother you boys anymore.

174
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:58,760
Ice cream!

175
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,080
Ice cream!

176
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:00,840
Ice cream!

177
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:01,360
Uncle!

178
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,040
Uncle, slow down!

179
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:02,600
Ice cream!

180
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,480
Can I get the coconut milk flavor?

181
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,800
Whoa! Those little punks.

182
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,240
They’re not studying. 

183
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:14,240
They’re reading comic books.

184
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:17,480
When you get home, 
I’m gonna whoop your ass.

185
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:21,880
155.
8TH GRADE

186
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:23,520
8TH GRADE

187
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:25,840
Hello, sir.

188
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:30,760
[MONDAY, MAY 18, 1998]

189
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:33,680
Ow!

190
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:36,920
Sir, are you mad at me or something?

191
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:39,360
175.

192
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:45,680
What’s his problem?

193
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:48,920
9TH GRADE

194
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:51,000
It’s already 
the second semester of 9th grade.

195
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:54,640
I finally get to transfer away from you guys.

196
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:55,960
Hey!

197
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,280
Don’t say that, August.

198
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:59,160
You have to stay with us forever.

199
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:00,680
I’m kidding.

200
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:03,720
Do you think we’ll end up 
in the same class in 10th grade?

201
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:05,560
Of course.

202
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,160
How can you be so sure?

203
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:11,960
We’ve taken the same exams every 
semester and gotten the exact same scores.

204
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:13,560
Wow. What a coincidence.

205
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:14,760
Coincidence, my ass.

206
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:16,600
You copy his answers every time.

207
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:18,720
True.

208
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:24,440
And I’m not even smart, so 
maybe we should find some smarter friends. 

209
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:27,960
I bet we’ll meet some in 10th grade.

210
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:37,480
So in 10th grade,
we move from this building to that one. 

211
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:40,320
And we start 
calling teachers “instructors,” right? 

212
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:41,160
But why?

213
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:42,720
Hey, and another thing. 

214
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:45,240
Have you noticed
how cute the 10th graders got? 

215
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:47,440
Totally different from 
when they were in 9th grade.

216
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,440
Dang!

217
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:53,800
I’m gonna love this!

218
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:55,640
(That’s right. It sounded so fun.)

219
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:58,120
It sounds freaking fun!

220
00:12:58,120 --> 00:13:02,160
(Until I met this guy.)

221
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:11,000
What’s your problem?

222
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:14,760
Didn’t you say you were walking home?

223
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:19,480
Hey, keep this in mind. 

224
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:21,560
I run this neighborhood.

225
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:35,360
People are trying to catch a snake 
at the alley entrance. Go help them.

226
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:41,440
Hey, are you trying to bug me?

227
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:45,160
He’s gonna learn his lesson.

228
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:47,120
Damn it.

229
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:50,040
Shit! A snake! A snake!

230
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:51,440
A snake!

231
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:56,840
Oh. It’s just a stick.

232
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:18,800
Yeah.

233
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:37,040
Let’s go, Augar.

234
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:40,720
Nothing’s stopping Ko today.

235
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:41,440
Come on.

236
00:14:41,520 --> 00:14:42,640
I’m gonna shine bright.

237
00:14:42,680 --> 00:14:43,760
Ko!

238
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:44,760
Yes?

239
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:47,360
Don’t go yet. Come here first.

240
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:48,280
What is it, Mom?

241
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:49,600
I need to ask you something.

242
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:54,160
Can you buy the things on this list for me?

243
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:57,040
What? No way. I’m going to play water fights.

244
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,240
My friends are waiting.

245
00:14:58,240 --> 00:15:00,000
Oh, come on. It’ll only take a minute.

246
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:03,640
Then you’ll go play with the boys
till late at night anyway. 

247
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:04,600
Yeah, you’re right, ma’am.

248
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:06,280
He’s too attached to us.

249
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:07,480
Exactly.

250
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:10,400
Please?

251
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:12,920
My handsome son?

252
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:15,760
Hey.

253
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:18,120
Why don’t you invite him along? 

254
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:19,440
You guys could be friends.

255
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:24,880
Nope. I already have enough friends.

256
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:30,880
Just wait a minute.

257
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:31,840
Sure.

258
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:35,040
Augar, give me a sec. 

259
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,400
I’m gonna go buy stuff for this madam.

260
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:43,960
I’m used to it, ma’am.

261
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:49,320
Don’t splash me. Don’t splash me.

262
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:50,320
Don’t splash me.

263
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:02,360
Uncle, did you do something illegal?

264
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:04,320
What are you talking about, Ko?

265
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:06,400
You’ve been served, sir.

266
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:11,720
Mm, that’s strange.

267
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:12,760
What’s strange, Uncle?

268
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:15,080
It’s for Tom Yum Kung 
that my mom likes to make.

269
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:19,120
It’s strange because that boy 
bought the exact same ingredients as you.

270
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:22,240
Hey.

271
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:25,760
Did you follow me here?

272
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:30,000
Why are you wearing the same shirt as me?

273
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:34,320
And why are you making 
Tom Yum Kung just like my mom? Huh?

274
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:36,200
My mom asked me 
to buy the ingredients for her.

275
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:39,280
And stop talking to me like that, Ko. 

276
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:41,520
Good.

277
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:43,560
So you know my name. 

278
00:16:43,680 --> 00:16:46,520
That means you know this is Ko’s territory.

279
00:16:46,520 --> 00:16:48,040
The uncle literally just said your name.

280
00:16:52,760 --> 00:16:56,680
Hey, don’t fight. You’re neighbors.

281
00:16:57,640 --> 00:16:58,560
Get along, you two.

282
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:00,240
Get along.

283
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:03,480
Stop bickering.

284
00:17:04,360 --> 00:17:04,920
Here, sir.

285
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:08,600
Thanks.

286
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:21,600
Bye, Uncle.

287
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:22,880
Wait, Ko.

288
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:24,040
Yeah, Uncle?

289
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:25,640
Did you forget something?

290
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:28,160
Oops. Almost did.

291
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:34,160
Hey.

292
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:34,960
Yes?

293
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:35,960
Your change.

294
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,800
Oh. Thank you.

295
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:42,640
See you, Uncle.

296
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:56,560
Please don’t splash me.

297
00:17:56,880 --> 00:17:58,520
Don’t splash me. Please, don’t.

298
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:01,960
Please don’t splash me. 

299
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:03,520
I’m bringing stuff home for my mom.

300
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:04,360
Please don’t splash me.

301
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:10,600
Go ahead. Shoot.

302
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:12,720
Bummer! I just ran out of water.

303
00:18:13,480 --> 00:18:14,000
Oh!

304
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:15,600
Please don’t splash me.

305
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:16,560
Don’t splash me.

306
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:20,120
Please don’t.

307
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:21,640
Whoa.

308
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:23,040
Please don’t splash me.

309
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:24,400
Please don’t splash me.

310
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:27,120
Don’t splash me.

311
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:29,520
Don’t splash me.

312
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:30,840
No water. No powder.

313
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:33,000
Please don’t.

314
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:39,400
What?

315
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:45,400
Please don’t splash me.

316
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:46,440
Spare me, please.

317
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:48,800
Gosh.

318
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:54,520
Hey!

319
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:57,440
Are you okay?

320
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:02,200
I got powder in my eyes. 

321
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:03,640
I can’t wipe it off with my dirty hands.

322
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:04,600
Let me.

323
00:19:05,280 --> 00:19:06,080
Keep your eyes closed.

324
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:12,280
No, that’s enough.

325
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:13,240
A little more.

326
00:19:14,040 --> 00:19:14,640
All right.

327
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:17,920
Stop shaking your head.

328
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:19,000
Here.

329
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:26,480
You okay now?

330
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:50,960
If you’re gonna join a water fight,
you need to be more careful.

331
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:53,560
You’ve gotta protect yourself, like Ko here. 

332
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:56,760
What?

333
00:19:57,160 --> 00:19:58,480
Don’t look at me like that.

334
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:01,440
I’m still dry because everyone 
around here respects my authority.

335
00:20:02,960 --> 00:20:04,360
Now, where’s my thank you?

336
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:07,080
Thank you.

337
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:11,400
Good.

338
00:20:12,080 --> 00:20:12,960
I’m taking off then.

339
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:18,040
See you.

340
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:50,200
Get on.

341
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:55,560
Hurry up before I change my mind.

342
00:20:56,240 --> 00:20:57,400
What about my bike?

343
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:08,080
Just leave it here. Nobody’s gonna steal it.

344
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:10,600
I know every house in this neighborhood.

345
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,480
- Uncle Toey.
- Yeah, Ko?

346
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,640
Can I leave this bike with you for now?

347
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:16,400
Sure.

348
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:17,920
He’ll come get it later.

349
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:23,480
All set.

350
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:29,800
No, no, no, no, no.

351
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:34,480
Someone like Ko doesn’t 
just give people rides that easily.

352
00:21:36,320 --> 00:21:36,760
Come on.

353
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:44,720
Let’s go, boy.

354
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:46,240
Go, go, go!

355
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:50,600
Pedal faster.

356
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,280
Speed up, turtle. 

357
00:21:58,360 --> 00:22:01,240
All your ingredients are here, ma’am.

358
00:22:01,240 --> 00:22:02,720
Wow.

359
00:22:02,840 --> 00:22:03,920
Thank you.

360
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:05,280
I’m heading out now. 

361
00:22:06,280 --> 00:22:07,560
Look at you. 

362
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:09,360
Always so quick with stuff like this.

363
00:22:10,040 --> 00:22:13,320
Hey. Take care of yourself, okay?

364
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:15,000
Songkran can get dangerous.

365
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:18,640
Nothing’s more dangerous than Ko, ma’am.

366
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:24,400
I’m hot, awesome, and dangerous.

367
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:28,520
Gosh. Like father, like son.

368
00:22:28,520 --> 00:22:30,560
Neither of them ever likes staying home.

369
00:22:31,360 --> 00:22:32,920
They just love going out.

370
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:35,320
When’s he coming back though?

371
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:36,200
No idea. 

372
00:22:36,280 --> 00:22:38,720
He’s probably out drinking 
with the sailor uncles who stayed ashore. 

373
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:40,760
Ah.  

374
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:43,160
Then I’ll come back later 
and keep you company.

375
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:46,400
I’m off now.

376
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:48,640
Okay.

377
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:50,720
Bye-bye.

378
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,160
Take care of yourself.

379
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:52,800
Yeah.

380
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:53,880
Don’t be naughty.

381
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:55,120
Yes, ma’am.

382
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:28,440
I’m not stealing it.

383
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:32,400
Let’s just call it payment
for washing that dude’s face. 

384
00:23:34,840 --> 00:23:37,720
But one orange isn’t gonna cut it.

385
00:24:24,720 --> 00:24:26,120
Tada!

386
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:28,840
Boss Ko finally has his own room. 

387
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:32,240
Boss Ko isn’t a kid anymore.

388
00:24:32,720 --> 00:24:34,280
Congratulations, Boss Ko.

389
00:24:34,960 --> 00:24:36,920
But we’ve both had
our own rooms since 5th grade. 

390
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:40,520
Smack your mouth for that, Augar. 

391
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:41,640
Don’t tease the boss.

392
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:49,080
If the opposite room belongs to that new boy,
Ko won’t be able to stand it.

393
00:24:49,360 --> 00:24:50,800
Just forget about that for now.

394
00:24:51,280 --> 00:24:52,800
There’s something important waiting for us.

395
00:24:56,640 --> 00:24:57,600
What did you bring?

396
00:24:58,240 --> 00:24:59,120
Here.

397
00:24:59,120 --> 00:25:00,040
Shit!

398
00:25:00,040 --> 00:25:02,120
Don’t! My mom can see.

399
00:25:02,120 --> 00:25:03,760
Just take a look first.

400
00:25:03,760 --> 00:25:04,720
Let me see that.

401
00:25:05,840 --> 00:25:06,720
Crap!

402
00:25:09,280 --> 00:25:10,320
What are you boys doing?

403
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:22,360
I just came to ask if anyone 
wants to go out on the boat with me.

404
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:28,600
Okay. I’ll just leave then.

405
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:35,520
Don’t let your mom know.

406
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:44,040
Keep it safe.

407
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:50,880
Hey.

408
00:25:51,680 --> 00:25:52,320
Nothing.

409
00:25:57,560 --> 00:26:00,160
Damn you, Augar.

410
00:26:01,320 --> 00:26:02,840
I’m sorry.

411
00:26:03,280 --> 00:26:04,480
I’ll just keep it to myself then.

412
00:26:05,320 --> 00:26:06,880
I was just afraid you guys would be bored.

413
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:10,000
I’m telling you, 
my dad isn’t gonna stop teasing me.

414
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:13,400
You’re gonna have your 
private room for only a day, big boss.

415
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:15,560
Isn’t that good?

416
00:26:15,560 --> 00:26:17,200
You get frightened easily, Ko.

417
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:19,520
Have you ever heard? 

418
00:26:20,360 --> 00:26:22,360
The first night you sleep alone… 

419
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:31,960
it will come to test how strong your heart is 
to see if you’re ready.

420
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:40,520
Who are you?

421
00:26:42,920 --> 00:26:44,080
I don’t know either.

422
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,040
Stop it, Augar!

423
00:26:51,800 --> 00:26:54,040
I shouldn’t have brought you guys up here.

424
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:55,160
What a mistake!

425
00:26:55,320 --> 00:26:56,680
But you only have us.

426
00:26:56,960 --> 00:26:57,560
Hey.

427
00:26:59,680 --> 00:27:02,800
All right. I’m sorry.

428
00:27:03,640 --> 00:27:04,760
I’m supposed to feel sorry.

429
00:27:06,280 --> 00:27:09,040
But I haven’t done anything wrong, big boss.

430
00:27:37,760 --> 00:27:38,960
Nobody’s home?

431
00:27:39,640 --> 00:27:41,360
I’m not sure. I think so.

432
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:42,680
Do you know the owner?

433
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:44,040
Can I leave this with you? 

434
00:27:44,760 --> 00:27:46,080
I still have another delivery to make.

435
00:27:46,560 --> 00:27:47,520
Thanks a lot, kid.

436
00:27:54,560 --> 00:27:55,960
That’s my name.

437
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:01,640
Let me put this away first.

438
00:28:03,800 --> 00:28:04,560
What now?

439
00:28:04,560 --> 00:28:05,400
Just a sec.

440
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:14,520
What did Dad order?

441
00:28:14,520 --> 00:28:16,760
[RECIPIENT: KO]

442
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:19,120
I bet he was too embarrassed 
to use his own name.

443
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:34,520
[AUNTIE PEN’S SHOP]

444
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:35,680
Look!

445
00:28:35,920 --> 00:28:37,560
So? Do I look good?

446
00:28:37,600 --> 00:28:41,440
Wow. You sure do.

447
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:44,960
You’re blinding us over here.

448
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:49,440
I can’t believe we’ll be in 10th grade.

449
00:28:50,160 --> 00:28:52,680
We need to build a bigger gang now 

450
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:55,240
since some of our people 
transferred schools.

451
00:28:55,920 --> 00:28:58,240
I just wanna smack them in the head.

452
00:28:58,880 --> 00:29:00,760
Before you build a new gang, 

453
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:03,480
how about learning 
how to button your shirt properly first?

454
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:09,000
By the way, where does 
your neighbor go to school?

455
00:29:11,280 --> 00:29:11,800
I don’t know.

456
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:13,840
I don’t know his name, his age, 

457
00:29:14,200 --> 00:29:15,320
or anything about him.

458
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:17,880
Are you guys really neighbors?

459
00:29:17,880 --> 00:29:20,520
I don’t need to know him. I don’t like him.

460
00:29:21,440 --> 00:29:22,760
What about you, Augar?

461
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:24,520
You keep asking about him. 

462
00:29:25,560 --> 00:29:26,280
You like him or something?

463
00:29:26,400 --> 00:29:27,560
Like him, my ass.

464
00:29:27,720 --> 00:29:28,960
I’ve only seen him from a distance.

465
00:29:29,120 --> 00:29:30,600
I haven’t even talked to him. 

466
00:29:31,360 --> 00:29:34,200
Hey, you need the uniform accessories too. 

467
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:35,280
Don’t take forever.

468
00:29:35,880 --> 00:29:37,440
All right. I’ll go pay now.

469
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:39,480
After you finish here, come with me.

470
00:29:40,760 --> 00:29:44,520
I’ve got a very important mission.

471
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:58,480
Hey.

472
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:00,920
Why don’t you use a stick?

473
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:04,440
It’s my first time buying. I’m sorry.

474
00:30:04,880 --> 00:30:05,840
Why are you apologizing? 

475
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:06,960
You didn’t do anything wrong.

476
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:10,040
I’ve never bought one on my own before.

477
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:12,000
I see.

478
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:15,080
Here. Use the stick and hook it like this.

479
00:30:24,600 --> 00:30:25,360
Thank you.

480
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:29,880
Are you new? 

481
00:30:30,120 --> 00:30:31,040
I don’t think I’ve seen you before.

482
00:30:31,840 --> 00:30:34,640
No. I’ve been going to 
the same school as you, Augar.

483
00:30:34,800 --> 00:30:35,080
Hm?

484
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:36,680
You know my name?

485
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:37,680
Of course.

486
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:39,840
You competed for 
the school basketball team in 9th grade.

487
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:42,400
Ah, you’re right.

488
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:43,880
What’s your name?

489
00:30:44,560 --> 00:30:45,000
Achi.

490
00:30:46,320 --> 00:30:47,680
Okay, Achi.

491
00:30:48,360 --> 00:30:49,800
I promise I’ll recognize you next time. 

492
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:51,360
You can come say hi to me anytime.

493
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:56,360
See you.

494
00:30:57,280 --> 00:30:59,240
Let’s see if we end up in the same class.

495
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:27,320
We’ve arrived.

496
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:32,120
So, this is the school supplies 
you were talking about?

497
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:37,000
Yeah! These are 
the school supplies I can’t live without.

498
00:31:37,120 --> 00:31:37,800
Gosh.

499
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:40,400
I seriously can’t with you.

500
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:46,920
Hey!

501
00:31:48,680 --> 00:31:49,520
That guy!

502
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:51,440
The new kid next door.

503
00:31:51,920 --> 00:31:52,720
Damn.

504
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:55,760
He’s pretty good-looking.

505
00:31:55,920 --> 00:31:58,400
How about we corner him
and threaten him into joining our gang? 

506
00:31:58,880 --> 00:32:03,320
If he says no, 
we’ll smack him with this thick book. 

507
00:32:03,320 --> 00:32:04,960
That’s your genius plan?

508
00:32:05,120 --> 00:32:06,240
Look at what he’s holding.

509
00:32:07,880 --> 00:32:10,920
He’ll crack your head open
before you even start threatening him. 

510
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:12,000
Shit.

511
00:32:13,560 --> 00:32:14,760
Does he go to a technical school?

512
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:17,480
What kind of nonsense is that?

513
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:22,040
Someone like Ko 
would never let that guy join our gang.

514
00:32:22,160 --> 00:32:24,640
Our gang only accepts real ones. 

515
00:32:26,040 --> 00:32:29,640
And the dude carrying 
a steel ruler is a robot? Dumbass.

516
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:31,760
Augar, slap your mouth. 

517
00:32:31,760 --> 00:32:32,960
How could you talk to Boss Ko like that?

518
00:32:33,680 --> 00:32:34,720
Enough already.

519
00:32:35,560 --> 00:32:37,760
Looks like I’ll have to teach him a lesson.

520
00:32:44,640 --> 00:32:46,480
What kind of lesson 
do you think Ko’s teaching him?

521
00:32:46,640 --> 00:32:47,400
Shhh.

522
00:32:47,960 --> 00:32:50,000
Gang members don’t question each other.

523
00:32:51,320 --> 00:32:52,280
All right.

524
00:32:52,720 --> 00:32:54,200
Get me a copy of One Piece.

525
00:32:54,680 --> 00:32:55,400
One Piece, my foot. 

526
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:56,480
Read Dragon Ball with me.

527
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:58,800
But I wanna read One Piece.

528
00:33:04,080 --> 00:33:05,080
Hey!

529
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:10,040
Watch it!

530
00:33:32,720 --> 00:33:34,160
Be more careful next time.

531
00:33:35,640 --> 00:33:36,800
Were you just calling me?

532
00:33:38,160 --> 00:33:38,880
No!

533
00:33:39,480 --> 00:33:40,320
I was calling my friend.

534
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:43,600
Where’d he go?

535
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:45,320
When I find him, 
I’m gonna smack him in the head.

536
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:55,920
What’s his deal?

537
00:34:06,960 --> 00:34:08,200
Can I have some of your ice cream?

538
00:34:08,720 --> 00:34:09,680
Eat your own.

539
00:34:10,200 --> 00:34:10,800
What?

540
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:22,320
What’s wrong, Boss Ko?

541
00:34:22,600 --> 00:34:24,320
Didn’t you just teach that guy a lesson?

542
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:26,520
Why are you sitting here 
looking all down now?

543
00:34:26,720 --> 00:34:28,160
Exactly.

544
00:34:28,720 --> 00:34:30,520
Maybe...

545
00:34:30,520 --> 00:34:31,360
Maybe what?

546
00:34:32,160 --> 00:34:33,400
Think before you talk.

547
00:34:34,400 --> 00:34:35,400
Nothing.

548
00:34:35,880 --> 00:34:38,080
So what exactly did you do?

549
00:34:39,720 --> 00:34:40,320
Nothing!

550
00:34:40,600 --> 00:34:42,760
I went over there, but he was gone.

551
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:45,400
- Ah!
- Ah!

552
00:34:49,200 --> 00:34:52,160
Hey, I’ve been wondering this forever. 

553
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:56,680
Why the hell do you guys 
always wear matching shirts?

554
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:59,480
We used to fight over clothes all the time.

555
00:34:59,480 --> 00:35:00,960
So my mom came up with a solution. 

556
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:03,920
She bought us the same clothes 
and made us wear matching outfits.

557
00:35:04,080 --> 00:35:05,240
I’m used to it now.

558
00:35:05,640 --> 00:35:06,840
It’s convenient for me too.

559
00:35:07,120 --> 00:35:08,360
I just wear whatever he wears. 

560
00:35:08,360 --> 00:35:09,840
I don’t have to think about it.

561
00:35:09,920 --> 00:35:10,800
Exactly.

562
00:35:11,680 --> 00:35:12,520
I see.

563
00:35:13,160 --> 00:35:14,080
Let’s head back.

564
00:35:14,840 --> 00:35:17,760
I wanna lie down on 
my fluffy bed in my new room.

565
00:35:17,960 --> 00:35:18,760
Fine. 

566
00:35:19,560 --> 00:35:23,440
But tonight, 
don’t forget to say your prayers, 

567
00:35:24,120 --> 00:35:25,360
or else...

568
00:35:25,360 --> 00:35:26,440
Stop it, Augar.

569
00:35:26,800 --> 00:35:27,680
I already forgot about that. 

570
00:35:27,680 --> 00:35:28,440
Why’d you have to bring it up again?

571
00:35:28,480 --> 00:35:29,200
I’m gonna kick you!

572
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:31,080
You bastard!

573
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:32,480
Ko, I’m sorry.

574
00:35:32,920 --> 00:35:34,160
Where are you guys going?

575
00:35:52,600 --> 00:35:54,040
Damn you, Augar!

576
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:55,480
Now it won’t leave my head.

577
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:05,160
Gosh, I can’t take this anymore! 

578
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:30,920
Wake up, Ko. It’s late.

579
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:40,960
Hey!

580
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:50,840
Why were you secretly 
watching me last night?

581
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:08,560
Ow!

582
00:39:12,400 --> 00:39:14,120
Ow, my arm.

583
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:21,280
When did I fall asleep? 

584
00:39:36,680 --> 00:39:38,680
(I went out on the boat 
with your dad at dawn.)

585
00:39:38,880 --> 00:39:40,200
(One of his workers took the day off.)

586
00:39:40,480 --> 00:39:43,120
(Today, your teacher’s making 
home visits before school starts.) 

587
00:39:43,240 --> 00:39:45,400
(Behave yourself, Ko.) 

588
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:46,920
Holy shit!

589
00:40:18,760 --> 00:40:21,040
[THAI LANGUAGE: GRADE 1]

590
00:40:21,040 --> 00:40:22,280
[THAI LANGUAGE: GRADE 6]

591
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:29,480
Sir, you must be tired.

592
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:30,840
Here’s some water.

593
00:40:36,040 --> 00:40:39,160
A troublemaker from 9th grade 
has turned into a better person.

594
00:40:39,560 --> 00:40:40,520
Of course, sir.

595
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:43,560
People can change.

596
00:40:44,960 --> 00:40:46,200
Can I really believe that?

597
00:40:48,080 --> 00:40:49,560
What kind of person do you think I am, sir?

598
00:40:55,200 --> 00:40:58,960
You’re reading Thai language books 
from Grades 1 through 9?

599
00:41:00,160 --> 00:41:01,720
Sometimes, sir.

600
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:04,160
There are lots of kids around here. 

601
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:06,000
I tutor them sometimes.

602
00:41:10,840 --> 00:41:13,680
Ko, my mom asked me to bring food over.

603
00:41:17,200 --> 00:41:18,600
I called out, but nobody answered. 

604
00:41:18,960 --> 00:41:21,920
The gate was open, so I just walked in.

605
00:41:22,280 --> 00:41:24,880
Are you Krittin’s neighbor?

606
00:41:24,960 --> 00:41:27,680
He’s my mom’s friend’s son. Don’t mind him.

607
00:41:28,120 --> 00:41:29,720
You can leave it there. 

608
00:41:29,960 --> 00:41:31,200
I’ll tell my mom when she gets back. 

609
00:41:31,200 --> 00:41:31,880
Thanks a lot.

610
00:41:36,240 --> 00:41:37,160
Hold on.

611
00:41:39,240 --> 00:41:40,040
May I ask you something?

612
00:41:41,120 --> 00:41:46,080
What’s Krittin, everyone’s beloved Ko, 
like at home? 

613
00:41:49,640 --> 00:41:50,600
Um...

614
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:52,840
Come on, sir.

615
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:54,120
He just moved here. 

616
00:41:54,120 --> 00:41:55,160
We’ve only known each other for a few days.

617
00:41:55,360 --> 00:41:56,440
I’m asking him.

618
00:42:01,960 --> 00:42:02,560
Well...

619
00:42:06,720 --> 00:42:07,760
He seems normal.

620
00:42:10,720 --> 00:42:12,760
He’s a good neighbor.

621
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:19,400
Oops!

622
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:26,760
He’s always helping me out.

623
00:42:30,760 --> 00:42:31,600
That’s enough.

624
00:42:34,560 --> 00:42:38,160
Ever since I moved here,
I’ve seen him stay up late every night.  

625
00:42:38,400 --> 00:42:41,040
His light’s always on. I think he’s studying. 

626
00:43:18,600 --> 00:43:20,600
Like Ko said, I just moved here. 

627
00:43:21,000 --> 00:43:26,320
I still don’t know much about him,
so please excuse me. 

628
00:43:26,320 --> 00:43:27,240
Goodbye, sir.

629
00:43:36,480 --> 00:43:37,440
See, sir? 

630
00:43:38,160 --> 00:43:40,160
People change.

631
00:43:43,680 --> 00:43:48,080
I hope you don’t go back to your 
troublemaking ways once school starts.

632
00:43:50,320 --> 00:43:53,320
Sir, would you like to 
stay and meet my parents?

633
00:43:54,680 --> 00:43:55,400
I don’t think so. 

634
00:43:56,280 --> 00:43:57,400
I still have a lot more houses to visit.

635
00:43:58,200 --> 00:43:59,320
- Sure.
- I’ll see you at school.

636
00:43:59,680 --> 00:44:00,200
Of course, sir.

637
00:44:00,320 --> 00:44:00,800
Okay?

638
00:44:01,200 --> 00:44:01,680
Yes.

639
00:44:02,280 --> 00:44:03,000
Goodbye, Mr. Kong.

640
00:44:03,120 --> 00:44:03,520
Bye.

641
00:44:29,960 --> 00:44:31,160
Returning the plate?

642
00:44:33,680 --> 00:44:34,400
Mm.

643
00:44:35,480 --> 00:44:36,200
Thanks.

644
00:44:37,920 --> 00:44:39,960
It’s alright. My mom made it.

645
00:44:42,040 --> 00:44:43,680
I mean...

646
00:44:44,600 --> 00:44:45,600
what you told the teacher.

647
00:45:27,600 --> 00:45:31,640
(Looks like this summer really is 
more special than all the summers before.)

648
00:45:46,280 --> 00:45:48,840
When’s Dad gonna finish 
moving all the stuff over here?

649
00:45:48,920 --> 00:45:50,880
I’m tired of going back and forth all the time.

650
00:45:51,000 --> 00:45:53,480
Just a few more days and we’ll be done. 

651
00:46:16,960 --> 00:46:19,360
(I don’t know if 
I should call it fate or something else.)

652
00:46:28,040 --> 00:46:29,600
(I don’t know
who could’ve arranged all this.) 

653
00:46:31,120 --> 00:46:31,600
Oops.

654
00:46:32,240 --> 00:46:33,040
What are you doing?

655
00:46:42,080 --> 00:46:43,800
(Maybe it’s just perfect timing.)

656
00:46:44,840 --> 00:46:45,960
I’m not stealing it.

657
00:46:46,840 --> 00:46:49,320
Let’s just call it payment 
for washing that dude’s face.

658
00:46:50,640 --> 00:46:53,320
But one orange isn’t gonna cut it.

659
00:47:20,600 --> 00:47:22,960
Mom, have you seen a package for me?

660
00:47:23,240 --> 00:47:24,160
I haven’t seen anything.

661
00:47:24,520 --> 00:47:26,160
(Maybe it’s all just a coincidence.)

662
00:47:31,840 --> 00:47:32,760
(But one thing’s for sure.)

663
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:36,200
(This summer,
everything seems to be going Ko’s way.)

664
00:47:44,000 --> 00:47:47,000
(I’m actually starting
to get excited about high school.)

665
00:48:00,400 --> 00:48:03,880
- Hi. My name’s Kanin Siritara. 
Or just Ko.

666
00:48:05,800 --> 00:48:07,640
- Hey, that new guy’s getting 
beat up by some 11th graders.

667
00:48:07,640 --> 00:48:08,200
- What?

668
00:48:08,840 --> 00:48:10,160
- What the hell?

669
00:48:12,800 --> 00:48:15,520
- I’ve already helped you 
twice now, you know.

670
00:48:16,720 --> 00:48:20,720
- Come pick me up tomorrow, Ko Song. 

671
00:48:20,720 --> 00:48:22,240
- Fine. I will. 
